Heat your oven to 200°C. Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat with a drizzle of
@oil{}. Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and fry, using a #spoon{} to
break up the mince. Cook until golden brown all over, ~{3-4%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw mince.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can}, pop half of them into a #bowl{} and
roughly mash them with the back of a #fork{} or a #potato masher{}.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{30%g} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the pork and
cook, stirring, for ~{1%min}.

Add the @water{150%ml} and the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @BBQ sauce{32%g} and
the whole and mashed beans with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring regularly, until thickened, ~{6-8%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g} coarsely and set aside.

Lay the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} on a #baking tray{} and pop
in the oven until warmed through, ~{3-4%mins}.

Heat the @lime & coriander basmati rice{1%package} according to pack
instructions.

Lay a warmed tortilla wrap in the middle of a wide piece of #foil{}. Add a
quarter of the rice in a line down the middle, followed by a quarter of the
pork mixture and a quarter of the cheese. Wrap them tightly up in the foil.
You can serve these as wraps without the foil if you prefer. Enjoy!